      "content": "15%? That's a pretty big swing. If I go to the Board with that kind of uncertainty and a potential drop in efficacy, they're almost certainly going to freeze the next round of funding to \"wait for more stability.\" They need to see a clear path to ROI here. \n\nIs that variance actually a dealbreaker, or is it just standard noise? Give it to me straight—can we characterize these results as stable enough to justify the investment, or is the volatility actually significant?",
